
Overview of verb haunt

The verb haunt has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (3) haunt, stalk -- (follow stealthily or recur constantly and spontaneously to; "her ex-boyfriend stalked her"; "the ghost of her mother haunted her")
2. (3) haunt, obsess, ghost -- (haunt like a ghost; pursue; "Fear of illness haunts her")
3. frequent, haunt -- (be a regular or frequent visitor to a certain place; "She haunts the ballet")

Overview of adj haunted

The adj haunted has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) haunted, obsessed, preoccupied, taken up -- (having or showing excessive or compulsive concern with something; "became more and more haunted by the stupid riddle"; "was absolutely obsessed with the girl"; "got no help from his wife who was preoccupied with the children"; "he was taken up in worry for the old woman")
2. haunted -- (showing emotional affliction or disquiet; "her expression became progressively more haunted")
3. haunted -- (inhabited by or as if by apparitions; "a haunted house")
